Amblyseius largoensis
is a generalist predator that feeds on a diversity of phytophagous mites, mainly those of the families Eriophyidae , Tenuipalpidae , and Tetranychidae , small insects and other food types , including pollen ( Rodriguez and Ramos 2004 ;
